lead_paragraph: Andre Drummond posted his NBA-leading 50th double-double with 15 points and 17 rebounds, and the Detroit Pistons built on a strong start from 3-point range to beat the Milwaukee Bucks 102-91 Saturday night.

headline.print_headline: 3-Point Shooting Helps Lift Pistons to 102-91 Win Over Bucks
